Sentencas: Investigation of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs) is receiving great attention due to its higher efficiency and zero environmental pollution during operation.
Titulo: Investigation on high entropy alloys as interconnect material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Interconnects are a critical part of the SOFC stack which connects the cells in series and combines the electricity produced.
Titulo: Investigation on high entropy alloys as interconnect material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The present study aims to investigate High Entropy Alloys (HEAs) for interconnect application in intermediate temperature SOFC.
Titulo: Investigation on high entropy alloys as interconnect material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Towards this, FeCoCrNi, FeCoCrNiMn0.1, FeCoCrNiMn0.5, and FeCoCrNiMn HEAs are prepared by vacuum arc melting and examined for its phase evaluation.
Titulo: Investigation on high entropy alloys as interconnect material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal stability, thermal expansion, resistivity, oxidation, and Area Specific Resistance (ASR) are investigated up to 800 degrees C. Oxidation studies show the formation of multi -component oxide in the HEAs which suppresses the growth of Cr2O3 layer.
Titulo: Investigation on high entropy alloys as interconnect material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: FeCoCrNiMn0.1, FeCoCrNiMn0.5, and FeCoCrNiMn HEAs possess ASR values less than 100 m ohm.cm2 in the temperature range of 600-800 degrees C which ensure the superior performance of the SOFC stack.(c) 2022
Titulo: Investigation on high entropy alloys as interconnect material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
